turns out that he was actually slated to be

32:17.755 --> 32:20.377
president. But I think the thing that saved us was 
he didn't know that. And we didn't either. Have you

32:25.041 --> 32:25.862
ever told him that? No. And so it was sort of like a 
soap opera. Every week we would wonder how we were

32:33.823 --> 32:37.028
doing in recruiting Herb Richardson. We'd have 
him and then we wouldn't have him. It's like

32:38.850 --> 32:40.393
landing a great big fish. And Gordy and I both knew 
that. We knew that if we could land Herb

32:43.317 --> 32:50.869
Richardson, steal the dean of engineering from 
MIT, we had made it. A&M had made it. And it was vital

32:53.734 --> 32:55.236
that we get him. So then we went to get Charlie 
Arnson for agriculture, and he was with, oh,

32:58.034 --> 33:07.789
what's that big company that he came from?

33:10.774 --> 33:12.116
He was their research director. It's a big ag 
corporation, and I can't think of the name.

33:16.403 --> 33:23.454
Anyway, but again, he was a member of the National 
Academy of Sciences, and Herb was a member of the

33:16.403 --> 33:23.454
National Academy of Engineering. That's the kind 
of quality we were looking for. And getting them

33:26.367 --> 33:30.191
both was a big moment. And to me, it represented the 
arrival of Texas A&M on the national scene. Good.

